"""Per-locale overrides for achievement copy.

The catalog in ``catalog.py`` is the *canonical* (English) source
of truth. This file layers locale-specific overrides on top so
that:

  1. Achievements that need rephrasing in another language (e.g.
     puns that don't translate, idiom that needs re-wording) get
     a polished RU version rather than a machine translation.
  2. New locales can be added by shipping one override dict.
  3. The seed script in ``seed.py`` writes all (achievement, locale)
     pairs into the ``achievement_i18n`` table on every startup;
     on a missing key, the engine falls back to the EN row from
     the catalog (which always exists as the canonical copy).

Structure: a tuple of 4-tuples ``(id, locale, title, description, reward)``.
Only achievements that need *non-default* copy in the target locale
are listed — others inherit the EN canonical copy.
"""

